pr_review_comment_body:
What about the case where the current directory is not writeable?

How about:
```python
if os.path.dirname(profile_path) == '':
    if not os.access(os.path.curdir):
        raise IOError("profile_path {} is not writeable.".format(os.path.curdir))
else:
    if not os.access(os.path.dirname(profile_path), os.W_OK):
        raise IOError("profile_path {} is not writeable.".format(profile_path))
```

