This needs to be switched around, "all" should be attached to the else block.
```
if name == 'new':
    return cls('New', reddit.get_new(limit=None), loader)

if name == 'all':
    sub = reddit.get_subreddit(name)
else:
    ...
```

I don't think this will work (see below), but that aside, here's a more concise way of doing the same thing:

    var partialSeries = {
      project: partialSeriesArray[0],
      signature: partialSeriesArray[1],
      visible: partialSeriesArray[2]
    }

The `patternNZHistory` is ensured to only keep the last `maxSteps` steps:

```
        // update pattern history
        patternNZHistory_.emplace_front(patternNZ.begin(), patternNZ.end());
        iterationNumHistory_.push_front(learnIteration_);
        if (patternNZHistory_.size() > maxSteps_)
        {
          patternNZHistory_.pop_back();
          iterationNumHistory_.pop_back();
        }
```

As a matter of fact, in the [Python implementation](https://github.com/numenta/nupic/blob/master/src/nupic/algorithms/sdr_classifier.py#L137), `maxSteps` is just a local variable in the constructor, and is used to created `patternNZHistory` as a `deque` with max length `maxSteps`.

